Package: cmdline.arguments
Title: Flexible and fully customizable commandline tool for R
 scripting and R based applications
Version: 0.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Oliver P.",
           family = "Madsen",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "Oliver.p.madsen@gmail.com")
Description: The cmdline.arguments package provides high-level functions
 for parsing arguments passed from the commandline. While other packages
 provide alternative interfaces for this purpose, the cmdline.arguments
 package lets the user specify any type of argument through its
 simplified interface while the modularized R6 interface allows advanced
 users to customize any part of the parser in a standardized manner.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
Depends:
    R6 (>= 2.1.0),
    rlang (>= 0.4.7)
Suggests: 
    covr,
    testthat
